        </item>
        <item>
         <widget class="QTextBrowser" name="textBrowser">
          <property name="minimumSize">
           <size>
            <width>230</width>
            <height>240</height>
           </size>
          </property>
          <property name="frameShape">
           <enum>QFrame::StyledPanel</enum>
          </property>
          <property name="html">
           <string>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 style=&quot; margin-top:14px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'SimSun'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:600;&quot;&gt;Advanced Parameter Instruction &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'SimSun'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:600;&quot;&gt;1. Cloth resolution&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'SimSun'; font-size:9pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Cloth resolution refers to the grid size (the unit is same as the unit of point clouds) of cloth which is used to cover the terrain. The bigger cloth resolution you have set, the coarser DTM you will get. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'SimSun'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:600;&quot;&gt;2. Max iterations&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'SimSun'; font-size:9pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Max iterations refers to the maximum iteration times of terrain simulation. 500 is enough for most of scenes. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'SimSun'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:600;&quot;&gt;3. Classification threshold&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'SimSun'; font-size:9pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Classification threshold refers to a threshold (the unit is same as the unit of point clouds) to classify the point clouds into ground and non-ground parts based on the distances between points and the simulated terrain. 0.5 is adapted to most of scenes. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
          </property>
          <property name="openExternalLinks">
           <bool>true</bool>
          </property>
